(10623, 914, 'team_6_bio', 'I\'m a Texan by birth, a New Yorker by choice, and proud of both. After two careers in newspapers and corporate PR, I moved to NYC (with a very understanding wife) in 2006 to write musicals. (Our five kids refer to it as "Dad\'s midlife crisis.")  In 2008, my longtime friend Nancy Lovell called with a little writing "jobbie," and I\'ve had the great privilege of writing for Nancy and Julie almost daily since. I\'m motivated to tell good stories for L-F clients that help our team gain positive, engaging exposure for them. I enjoy guiding our materials through the editing process to get the best press pieces we can. And I love working with the L-F family.'),
