(430, 1, '2017-04-14 22:32:05', '2017-04-14 22:32:05', 'We would like to invite you to the Red Carpet Screening &amp; junket of MIRACLES FROM HEAVEN Feb 20/21 in Dallas (full details, below). Talent attending include: Jennifer Garner, DeVon Franklin, Bishop TD Jakes, the real life Beam family.\r\n\r\nMIRACLES FROM HEAVEN is based on the incredible true story and memoir of Christy Beam (Jennifer Garner). When Christy discovers her 10-year-old daughter Anna (Kylie Rogers) has a rare, incurable disease, she becomes a ferocious advocate for her daughters healing as she searches for a solution. As Christy searches she befriends Angela Bradford (Queen Latifah), who helps bring everyday joy and hope back to the Beam family. After Anna has a freak accident, an extraordinary miracle unfolds in the wake of her dramatic rescue that leaves medical specialists mystified, her familys faith restored and their community inspired. Also starring Martin Henderson, John Carroll Lynch and Eugenio Derbez. Directed by Patricia Riggen. Screenplay by Randy Brown based on the book by Christy Beam. Produced by Joe Roth, T.D. Jakes and DeVon Franklin.\r\n\r\nSaturday, Feb 20\r\n\r\n4:30 -- Privately screen MIRACLES FROM HEAVEN, followed by Q&amp;A w/ the Beams\r\n7:00 -- Dinner\r\n\r\nSunday, Feb 21\r\n8:30 AM -- Depart for The Potter\'s House church service w/ Bishop Jakes\r\n\r\n9:00 AM -- Potter\'s House service w/ Bishop Jakes (Jennifer Garner attending as well)\r\n\r\n11:30 AM -- Church service ends\r\n\r\n11:45 AM -- Lunch\r\n\r\n1:30 PM -- Depart for theater for red carpet\r\n\r\n1:45 PM -- Media check-in to red carpet\r\n\r\n2:00 PM -- Red carpet begins (talent include: Jennifer Garner, DeVon Franklin, Bishop TD Jakes, the Beam family)\r\n\r\n3:30 PM -- Screening begins for general public\r\n\r\n3:30 PM -- Junket takes place during screening\r\n\r\n5:35 PM -- Junket concludes, talent go to Q&amp;A in auditorium\r\n\r\n5:40 PM -- Screening concludes, Q&amp;A', 'Miracles From Heaven - Da