(1126, 3, '2017-07-14 17:21:00', '2017-07-14 17:21:00', 'Greg Laurie: Harvest Ministries has partnered with the Erwin Brothersthe filmmakers that produced <em>October Baby</em>, <em>Moms\' Night Out</em>, and <em>Woodlawn</em>to bring you the new feature film <em>Steve McQueen: </em><em>American Icon</em>.\r\n\r\nSteve McQueen truly is an American icon. Recently, <em>Esquire</em> Magazine noted that even 50 years after his career\'s peak, Steve McQueen "is still the King of Cool." Despite abounding biographies and articles on the acting legend\'s life, many people are unaware that Steve McQueen was a believer in Jesus Christ.\r\n\r\nOn the surface he had everythingglobal fame, cars, homes, more money than he could spend in a lifetimebut he also had a hole in his heart. He was the highest paid movie star in the world, but he was not happy or complete until he became a Christian.\r\n\r\nGreg Laurie states, "That is the story I want to tell in this filma story people have never seen before." Producer and director Jon Erwin said, "This film will be a one-night, nationwide cinematic event that will invade hundreds, perhaps a thousand theaters this fall. And most importantly, it will create an opportunity for Pastor Greg to use the story of how Steve McQueen found redemption and hope, and offer that same gospel message to the live theater audience."', 'Steve McQueen: American Icon', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'steve-mcqueen-american-icon', '', '', '2017-07-14 18:00:02', '2017-07-14 18:00:02', '', 0, 'http://lovell-fairchild.dev/?post_type=clients&#038;p=1126', 4, 'clients', '', 0),
